    <part>
        <title>Introduction</title>

        <chapter>
            <title>Pogamut</title>

            <section>
                <title>Purpose of this book</title>

                <para>This book is intended as cookbook for both the core
        PogamutUT2004 library and for Pogamut Netbeans plugin that is created
        to support development of Pogamut bots. However if you skip the
        Netbeans related parts you can use this book as extended comment of
        example bots distributed with the Pogamut library.
                </para>
            </section>

            <section>
                <title>How to use it</title>

                <para>Book is separated into stand alone tutorials, after completing
        each tutorial you will learn about one new functionality of the
        Pogamut library in conjunction with how to use the Netbeans plugin. It
        is adviced to have the source code of described bots open in the IDE
        to be able to quickly switch between the tutorial and the bot's source
        code.
                </para>
            </section>
        </chapter>

